           <li>{{ city }}: {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
         {% endfor %}</ul>
 
+    Like the :func:`~jinja-filters.sort` filter, sorting and grouping is
+    case-insensitive by default. The ``key`` for each group will use the
+    case of the first item encountered in each group. This can be
+    disabled by passing ``case_sensitive=True``.
+
+    If ``with_counts`` is set to ``True``, each group is a
+    ``(grouper, list, count)`` tuple instead, where ``count`` is the
+    number of items in the group. This avoids needing to write
+    ``|list|length`` in the template to get the size of a group.
+
+    .. sourcecode:: jinja
+
+        <ul>{% for city, items, count in users|groupby("city", with_counts=True) %}
+          <li>{{ city }} ({{ count }}): {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
+        {% endfor %}</ul>
+
+    .. versionchanged:: 3.1
+        Added the ``case_sensitive`` parameter.
+
+    .. versionchanged:: 3.1
+        Added the ``with_counts`` parameter.
+
     .. versionchanged:: 3.0
         Added the ``default`` parameter.
 
